      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know, i know... the \"reach out for help\" thing. but it's not like i'm in immediate danger or anything. it's just the logic of it all. i look at my slack notifications, my email, my calendar... it's all just data. if the data stops flowing, the system just keeps running. it makes me feel like there's no difference between me being here or me just... not being. like, does it even matter if an empty chair is occupied if no one is actually looking at it?",
